---
/**
 * context-engineering 0008 · Figure 1 — the hero "three machines, three cost
 * dials" diagram (text → embed → vector → ANN index, with the cost band).
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from
 * docs/context-engineering/lessons/0008-embeddings-indexing-and-cost.html
 * (figure + svg + figcaption incl. the footnote <sup>). It lives as an .astro
 * component, NOT inline in the MDX, because MDX's JSX parser is unreliable with
 * raw inline SVG that uses kebab-case attributes (text-anchor, font-size,
 * stroke-width, marker-end, …). In an .astro file the SVG is plain HTML, so it
 * renders byte-for-byte.
 *
 * The source page defined the arrowhead markers ONCE in a shared <defs> block at
 * the top of the document <body> (ids: arw, arwG, arwR, arwM). The MDX has no
 * such shared block, so the markers this figure references (arw, arwG, arwM) are
 * inlined into its own <defs>.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 640 290"
        role="img"
        aria-label="Text is embedded into a vector, stored in an approximate-nearest-neighbour index, and queried; each stage carries a cost."
    >
        <defs>
            <marker
                id="arw"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#6b675f"></path></marker
            >
            <marker
                id="arwG"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#2f5d3a"></path></marker
            >
            <marker
                id="arwM"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#b5179e"></path></marker
            >
        </defs>
        <!-- text -->
        <rect
            x="24"
            y="40"
            width="150"
            height="58"
            rx="10"
            fill="#efe7f0"
            stroke="#111110"
            stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
        <text x="99" y="64" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >Chunk of text</text
        >
        <text x="99" y="82" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
            >"reset the user token"</text
        >
        <!-- embedder -->
        <rect
            x="220"
            y="40"
            width="160"
            height="58"
            rx="10"
            fill="#f1eef2"
            stroke="#b5179e"
            stroke-width="2"></rect>
        <text x="300" y="62" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" font-weight="700" fill="#b5179e"
            >Embedding model</text
        >
        <text x="300" y="80" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
            >text &rarr; vector · costs tokens</text
        >
        <!-- vector -->
        <rect x="430" y="40" width="186" height="58" rx="10" fill="#eef2f7" stroke="#1f3a5a"></rect>
        <text x="523" y="60" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" font-weight="700" fill="#1f3a5a"
            >Vector</text
        >
        <text x="523" y="78" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
            >[0.02, -0.41, … ] · 1536 dims</text
        >
        <line x1="174" y1="69" x2="216" y2="69" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
        <line x1="380" y1="69" x2="426" y2="69" stroke="#b5179e" marker-end="url(#arwM)"></line>

        <!-- store -->
        <rect x="430" y="140" width="186" height="64" rx="10" fill="#e9f3ec" stroke="#2f5d3a"
        ></rect>
        <text x="523" y="164" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" font-weight="700" fill="#2f5d3a"
            >ANN index (vector store)</text
        >
        <text x="523" y="182" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
            >millions of vectors · HNSW / IVF / PQ</text
        >
        <text x="523" y="196" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
            >recall &harr; latency &harr; memory</text
        >
        <line x1="523" y1="98" x2="523" y2="138" stroke="#2f5d3a" marker-end="url(#arwG)"></line>

        <!-- query -->
        <rect
            x="24"
            y="150"
            width="150"
            height="58"
            rx="10"
            fill="#efe7f0"
            stroke="#111110"
            stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
        <text x="99" y="174" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >User query</text
        >
        <text x="99" y="192" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
            >embedded the same way</text
        >
        <line x1="174" y1="179" x2="426" y2="175" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
        <text x="300" y="168" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" font-style="italic" fill="#6b675f"
            >find the nearest vectors</text
        >

        <!-- cost band -->
        <rect x="24" y="240" width="592" height="34" rx="8" fill="#fbecec" stroke="#9a2417"></rect>
        <text x="320" y="262" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10.5" font-weight="700" fill="#9a2417"
            >Every arrow is a bill: embed tokens · store memory · search compute · then the LLM
            tokens downstream</text
        >
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        Semantic retrieval is three machines with three cost dials. <b>Embed</b> turns meaning into geometry,
        the <b>index</b> finds neighbours approximately, and the whole loop bills you in tokens, memory,
        and latency.<sup><a href="#s2" id="r1b">2</a></sup>
    </figcaption>
</figure>
